
Step 1) git submodules update --init --recursive

Step 2) adjust the urls in .git/config if you don't want a read-only checkout

Step 3) Run ./configure or ./configure-release script from the top level

Step 4) cd build or buildrelease

Step 5) make # Parallel builds tested up to -j30

Each of the several submodules inside "compiler" starts at a commit, rather than
a named branch.  You can checkout master in each of them to get on the master branch,
and then pull them.
